ToroidZip — Roadmap
===================

## Status: Milestone 1 complete

---

### Milestone 1 — Baseline encoder ✓
- Anchor + ratio computation
- Boundary classification (Identity / Normal / Pole-Zero / Pole-Inf)
- Raw float64 ratio stream with periodic re-anchoring (default K=256)
- Lossless round-trip decoder
- Tests passing, benchmarks wired
- CLI scaffold

### Milestone 2 — Entropy coding
- Implement rANS (range Asymmetric Numeral Systems) encoder/decoder
- Ratio distribution model (Laplace centered at 1.0 as starting point)
- Pole event sidecar format (separate from main entropy stream)
- Verify lossless round-trip with entropy coding
- First real compression ratios

### Milestone 3 — Benchmarking
Compare against: raw float64, delta encoding, zstd, brotli, fpzip

Target data classes:
1. Smooth floating-point time series (IoT/sensor)
2. Scientific measurement data (multi-order-of-magnitude range)
3. Financial tick data
4. Neural network weight tensors

Metrics: compression ratio, encode MB/s, decode MB/s

### Milestone 4 — Analysis and iteration
- Identify winning/losing data classes and root causes
- Adaptive entropy model
- Explore error management options (compensated multiply, lossy mode)

### Milestone 5 — Formalization
- Algorithm writeup with mathematical basis
- Integration guide (library API)

---

## CLI flags

    toroidzip encode [--reanchor-interval N] <input.f64> <output.tzrz>
    toroidzip decode <input.tzrz> <output.f64>

`--reanchor-interval N` (default 256): lower = more accurate reconstruction,
larger file. Higher = smaller file, more cumulative float drift between anchors.

